suggestions.description:
App.jsx line 1097, inside the teamVibe.key useEffect:

  const VIBE_LABELS = { 'after-hours': 'After Hours', 'slow-day': 'Slow Day', ... }

This is a pure static mapping with zero dependency on any variable. It is recreated on every vibe change. Move it to module scope alongside VIBE_COLORS, VIBE_RANK, and the other VIBE_* constants. This also makes it available for potential reuse in StatsBar or the VibeSparkline tooltip.

App.jsx lines 39-40:
  // WORKER_CONFETTI_PIECES removed -- worker confetti now uses CONFETTI_PIECES
  // with worker color applied via CSS custom property on the container

This migration-era comment explains a change that already happened. The code it references no longer exists. Delete it.
